      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 814: connectDeviceStartIce overwrites answerRetryTimer_ without cancelling any existing retry timer for the same ConnectionInfo. If connectDeviceStartIce can be called again for an existing info before the previous attempt is fully shut down, the old timer handler remains queued and still owns devicePk/value through the bound handler. It can re-announce an obsolete request and race with the new attempt\u0027s answerRetries_ counter. Cancel/reset the old timer before creating a new one.\n```suggestion\n        if (info-\u003eanswerRetryTimer_)\n            info-\u003eanswerRetryTimer_-\u003ecancel();\n        info-\u003eanswerRetries_ \u003d 0;\n        info-\u003eanswerRetryTimer_ \u003d std::make_unique\u003casio::steady_timer\u003e(*config_-\u003eioContext,\n                                                                       std::chrono::steady_clock::now()\n                                                                           + DHT_MSG_RETRY_INTERVAL);\n```",
