      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 848: retryRequestOnNoAnswer holds info-\u003emutex_ while calling dht()-\u003eputEncrypted() and arming the next async_wait. This expands the critical section across external/asynchronous DHT code and can block or deadlock if putEncrypted synchronously invokes code that needs the same ConnectionInfo lock or otherwise performs non-trivial work. Capture the required state under the lock, then release it before doing the DHT put and timer scheduling.\n```suggestion\n    bool shouldRetry \u003d false;\n    unsigned retryCount \u003d 0;\n    {\n        std::lock_guard lk(info-\u003emutex_);\n        if (!info-\u003ewaitingForPeerResponse_ || info-\u003eresponseReceived_ || !info-\u003eonConnected_)\n            return;\n        retryCount \u003d ++info-\u003eanswerRetries_;\n        shouldRetry \u003d retryCount \u003c DHT_MSG_MAX_RETRIES \u0026\u0026 info-\u003eanswerRetryTimer_;\n    }\n\n    auto deviceId \u003d devicePk-\u003egetLongId();\n    if (config_-\u003elogger)\n        config_-\u003elogger-\u003edebug(\"[device {}] No answer to connection request, re-announcing it ({}/{})\",\n                               deviceId,\n                               retryCount,\n                               DHT_MSG_MAX_RETRIES);\n    // putEncrypted and async_wait happen after releasing info-\u003emutex_.\n```",
